The paper discusses a novel neural network architecture that focuses on robustness to adversarial input, which is a common concern in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The approach involves forcing the network to make predictions and subsequently testing those predictions, which is a technique used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). Additionally, the paper discusses the issue of adversarial attacks, which is a topic in computer security (cs.CR).
